    • Method Detail

      • fullyExpand

        public static java.util.Map<TupleTag<?>,PCollection<?>> fullyExpand(java.util.Map<TupleTag<?>,PValue> partiallyExpanded)
        Returns all the tagged PCollections represented in the given PValue.

        For backwards-compatibility, PCollectionView is still a "PValue" to users, which occurs in only these places:

        • POutput.expand() (users can write custom POutputs)
        • PInput.expand() (users can write custom PInputs)
        • PTransform.getAdditionalInputs() (users can have their composites report inputs not passed by PCollection.apply(org.apache.beam.sdk.transforms.PTransform<? super org.apache.beam.sdk.values.PCollection<T>, OutputT>))

        These all return Map<TupleTag<?> PValue>. A user's implementation of these methods is permitted to return either a PCollection or a PCollectionView for each PValue. PCollection's expand to themselves and PCollectionView expands to the PCollection that it is a view of.
